{{item:3026}} {{item:3508}} {{item:3031}} {{item:3036}} {{item:3156}} {{item:3139}} {{item:3033}} {{item:3046}} {{item:3094}} {{item:3085}} {{item:3087}} {{item:3072}} 

Plus ad champions have greater variety in boot options than AP (at least, they sacrifice less).

I wouldn't say {{item:3027}} or {{item:3151}} are garbage. They are great items, just not ment for everyone. RoD is fine honestly, as it provides a good amount of AP, health, mana and because of the charging mechanic is pretty cheap. Torment is an item for DoT champs, but as it's the only option for some flat magic penetration everyone buyes it.

The others spot on. I especially hate deathcap, such a lame excuse of an item to limit mages AP early game scaling.

But what mages really need is more defined 'build' sets, like how ADC got on-hit build, crit build and Penetration build. Three different build with just some minor overlap, And besides those they got several defensive options; {{item:3155}} for some MR and a shield, {{item:3814}} for some MR and a spell shield, {{item:3139}} for some MR and a cc-removal, {{item:3026}} for some armour and a Ress. Mages got {{item:3157}} for Armour and {{item:3102}} for MR + spellshield.

The lack of mage items is even cleared if you would look at components that can only be build in to 1 item;
{{item:3191}} -> {{item:3157}} 
{{item:3136}} -> {{item:3151}} 
{{item:3802}} -> {{item:3165}} 

I'm pretty sure AD items don't have any of them.

For the % penetration items, I don't think they have to be removed, but making it much less of an 'enemy has armour/MR, lets buy last whisper/void' item. That if you opt for going penetration you will deal a lot more damage against tanks then if you wouldn't, but less damage against enemies with low resistance. This would I think be much healthier for the game, as now it's just 'let's buy it and destroy everyone at the same time' item (especially for ADC's).
